comments.body:
This would be a bit more idiomatic as an abstract base class
```dart
abstract class IOSMigrator {
  final Logger logger;

  bool migrate();

  String processLine(String line);

  void processFileLines(File file)  {
    // as before.
  }
}

// You can chain them together:
class IOSMigration {
  IOSMigration(this.migrators);

  final List<IOSMigrator> migrators;

  void run() {
    for (final IOSMigrator migrator in migrators) {
      if (!migrator.migrate()) {
        // This class would encapsulate logic for aborting/rolling-back the transaction.
      }
    } 
  }
}
```

